<Layout title="SCPP">
    <section class="py-16 relative">
        <div class="absolute top-48 left-96 lg:w-96 h-full hero-bg -z-10"></div>
        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:grid grid-cols-2">
                <div>
                    <h1 class="text-7xl font-bold mb-10 font-dotgothic16">
                        SCPP
                    </h1>
                    <p>
                        Personal Budget Control System. With its Android app and
                        Windows desktop version, SCPP offers you the flexibility
                        to record your expenses, income, and savings anytime and
                        anywhere.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-video">
                    <video src="/portfolio/video/scpp.mp4" autoplay muted
                    ></video>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <CrazyLine />
    <section class="pb-6">
        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <div class="flex flex-col-reverse md:grid grid-cols-3">
                <DotLottiePlayer
                    src="/portfolio/img/money-2.lottie"
                    autoplay
                    client:visible
                    className="max-w-72 self-center"
                />
                <div class="col-span-2">
                    <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-10">The Problem</h2>
                    <p>
                        SCPP arose from the need for a simple solution to
                        efficiently control expenses. It is a straightforward
                        and up-to-date tool for accurate personal finance
                        tracking.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Although there are many applications on the market, none
                        met the specific requirements sought due to their
                        complexity or costly subscriptions. That's why I created
                        a customized option for managing my finances.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="py-16">
        <div class="container mx-auto">
            <div class="flex flex-col md:grid grid-cols-3 gap-10">
                <div class="col-span-2">
                    <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-10">Architecture</h2>
                    <p>
                        The architecture of SCPP is based on a Node.js API, a
                        microservice that facilitates access to the MySQL
                        database.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        SCPP includes a mobile application for Android developed
                        in React Native. It allows you to view, add, and edit
                        expense information, offers financial graphs, and
                        provides search functions by category or keywords,
                        delivering a comprehensive experience for personal
                        financial tracking.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The platform also offers a desktop application in C#
                        with WinUI3 that replicates the functions of the mobile
                        version and adds interaction with graphs and detailed
                        visualization. It provides a comprehensive experience
                        for financial analysis and management, allowing users to
                        track their finances through their computer.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <Image src={ScppArch} alt="" class="self-center" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <Waves wavesOpacity={[0.5, 0.7, 0.9]} />
    <section class="bg-sky-950 py-10">
        <div id="bubbles">
            <div class="bubble x1"></div>
            <div class="bubble x2"></div>
            <div class="bubble x3"></div>
